sql:
SELECT owners.owner_name, campaigns.campaign_name
FROM campaigns
INNER JOIN owners ON campaigns.owner_id = owners.owner_id;

SELECT campaigns.campaign_name, campaign_types.campaign_type_name
FROM campaigns
INNER JOIN campaign_types ON campaigns.campaign_type_id = campaign_types.campaign_type_id;

external_knowledge:
- "key metric" refers to 'Metric 1';
- "exceptionally well" means having an average performance value greater than 5000;
- "specific funding and budget constraints" refer to campaigns that belong to 'Budget Category 1' or 'Budget Category 2';
- "ongoing campaigns" are those that were started in 2020 and are not in the 'Completed' status.
